'''Adrián Bernabé Garcia''' (born May 26, 2001) is a Spanish football [[midfielder]] who currently plays for [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]].
==Career==
A youth product of [[RCD Espanyol]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-espana.net/71044/barcas-bernabe-join-man-city|title=Barca's Bernabe to join Man City|date=16 April 2018|work=football-espana.net |accessdate=8 January 2019}}</ref> and ''[[La Masia]],'' the [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] academy, Bernabé joined Manchester City in the summer of 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.talksport.com/football/360986/transfer-report-manchester-city-agree-deal-sign-16-year-old-barcelona-starlet-adrian/|title=Man City ‘agree deal’ to sign Barcelona midfielder - Reports|date=17 April 2018|work=talkSport |accessdate=22 October 2018}}</ref> An attacking midfielder, Bernabé joined the first team in pre-season playing against [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] and played in the [[EFL Trophy]] against [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/first-team-news/2018/september/who-is-adrian-bernabe-manchester-city-player?|title=Who is Man City youngster Adrian Bernabe?|work=Manchester City F.C. |date=25 September 2018 |accessdate=22 October 2018}}</ref> On the 25 September 2018, Bernabé came on as a late substitute in the [[EFL Cup]] against [[Oxford United F.C.|Oxford United]], his first senior appearance for Manchester City.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/match-report/2018/september/oxford-united-v-man-city-carabao-cup-round-3-match-report|title=Oxford United v Manchester City Match Report|work=Manchester City F.C. |date=25 September 2018 |accessdate=22 October 2018 |author=David Clayton}}</ref>
